(Apologies for any typos, 16-06-2008. :)

This project is a kids level Parallel Port Experimental Board.
It can be built on the kitchen table and only basic standard electronic
tools are required.

Phase two, the MASTER CLOCK construction.

It will be easily capable of working on an older PC with a Parallel Port
and there will be some code to use it eventually in this format using
MS-DOS (TM) and the interpreter QBASIC.EXE. For the time being however
it will be dedicated to the classic AMIGA range of computers.

Enjoy...

(The next part will be the built-in PC compatible simple regulated 5V(ish)
supply rail and other rails also. This can also be used in AMIGA mode. :)

